title: Pinnacles National Park: Insects
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Insects                Insects, Spiders, Centipedes, and Millipedes                   Moths               Tarantulas             Although often overlooked, invertebrates comprise many thousands of wildlife species at Pinnacles. Their lack of bones, teeth, fur, and feathers may make them seem primitive, but don’t be fooled. In many cases their life histories are just as complex as those of larger animals, and often much more bizarre. And they are usually much easier to find and observe than larger wildlife.  To read more click here.   Dragonflies and Damselflies Butterflies Bees Ladybugs
